HB239 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to the salaries of public education employees;
5 to provide for a revision of the State Minimum Salary Schedule
6 to reflect a pay increase of two percent beginning with the
7 fiscal year 2026-2027; to provide that each employee of
8 certain boards of education shall receive the pay increase
9 according to placement on the appropriate salary step; to
10 require the appropriate increases on the State Minimum Salary
11 Schedule; to provide support employees with a two percent pay
12 increase beginning with the fiscal year 2026-2027; to require
13 salary schedules; to provide the employees of certain other
14 public educational institutions and schools with a two percent
15 pay increase for the 2026-2027 fiscal year; to provide for an
16 across the board salary increase on all two-year postsecondary
17 salary schedules; to establish other requirements on the
18 two-year postsecondary salary schedules; to establish
19 miscellaneous pay provisions relating to public education; and
20 to provide for a funded one-time longevity bonus payment in
21 addition to the retirement benefits of certain retirees and
22 beneficiaries of the Teachers' Retirement System.
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
24 Section 1. PAY INCREASES, FY 2026-2027. The State
25 Budget Officer shall allocate to the State Board of Education,
