87 All certificated employees, including the Adult Basic
88 Education and Science in Motion employees, shall be guaranteed
89 pay increases in the amounts indicated above for their years
90 of experience and degrees earned and the corresponding pay
91 increases shall be reflected in the appropriate local salary
92 schedule and paid to each certificated employee. The
93 provisions and requirements of this act shall be in addition
94 to the provisions of Section 16-13-231.1, Code of Alabama
95 1975, relating to the State Minimum Salary Schedule. Each
96 certificated employee shall be properly placed on the local
97 salary schedule according to degree earned and years of public
98 education service (either in-state or out-of-state), which
99 shall be not less than the amounts appropriated for the State
100 Minimum Salary Schedule. The employee shall be paid according
101 to degree earned and length of public education experience.
102 The pay increase shall be given to each person employed for
103 the 2026-2027 fiscal year in addition to any state or local
104 step increase to which the employee is otherwise entitled. The
105 local board of education shall transmit to the State
106 Department of Education the appropriate notice of the earned
107 advanced degree for each employee in a timely fashion;
108 thereafter, the employee shall be paid for the advanced degree
109 as soon as the degree is certified to the State Department of
110 Education as being earned.
